Batch Bayesian Active Learning by Disagreement (BatchBALD)#

 9 import numpy as np
10 from matplotlib import pyplot as plt, animation
11 from sklearn.datasets import make_blobs
12
13 from skactiveml.utils import MISSING_LABEL, labeled_indices, unlabeled_indices
14 from skactiveml.visualization import plot_utilities, plot_decision_boundary, \
15     plot_contour_for_samples
16
17 from sklearn.gaussian_process import GaussianProcessClassifier
18 from sklearn.ensemble import BaggingClassifier
19 from skactiveml.classifier import SklearnClassifier
20 from skactiveml.pool import BatchBALD
21
22 random_state = np.random.RandomState(0)
23
24 # Build a dataset.
25 X, y_true = make_blobs(n_samples=200, n_features=2,
26                        centers=[[0, 1], [-3, .5], [-1, -1], [2, 1], [1, -.5]],
27                        cluster_std=.7, random_state=random_state)
28 y_true = y_true % 2
29 y = np.full(shape=y_true.shape, fill_value=MISSING_LABEL)
30
31 # Initialise the classifier.
32 clf = SklearnClassifier(BaggingClassifier(
33     SklearnClassifier(GaussianProcessClassifier(), random_state=random_state),
34     random_state=random_state),
35     classes=np.unique(y_true),
36     random_state=random_state
37 )
38 # Initialise the query strategy.
39 qs = BatchBALD(random_state=random_state)
40
41
42 # Preparation for plotting.
43 fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, constrained_layout=True)
44 feature_bound = [[min(X[:, 0]), min(X[:, 1])], [max(X[:, 0]), max(X[:, 1])]]
45 artists = [[] for j in range(5)]
46
47 # The active learning cycle:
48 n_cycles = 5
49 for c in range(n_cycles):
50     # Fit the classifier.
51     clf.fit(X, y)
52
53     # Get labeled instances.
54     X_labeled = X[labeled_indices(y)]
55
56     # Query the next instance/s.
57     query_idx, utilities = qs.query(X=X, y=y, ensemble=clf, batch_size=4, return_utilities=True)
58
59     # Plot the labeled data.
60     for i, ax in enumerate(axs.flatten()):
61         coll_old = list(ax.collections)
62         plot_contour_for_samples(X, utilities[i], res=25,
63                                  feature_bound=feature_bound, replace_nan=None, ax=ax)
64         ax.scatter(X[:, 0], X[:, 1], c=y_true, cmap="coolwarm", marker=".",
65                    zorder=2)
66         ax.scatter(X_labeled[:, 0], X_labeled[:, 1], c="grey", alpha=.8,
67                    marker=".", s=300)
68         ax = plot_decision_boundary(clf, feature_bound, ax=ax)
69         ax.set_title(f"Batch {c+1}, Utilities[{i}]")
70
71         for x in ax.collections:
72             if x not in coll_old:
73                 artists[c].append(x)
74
75     # Label the queried instances.
76     y[query_idx] = y_true[query_idx]
77
78 ani = animation.ArtistAnimation(fig, artists, interval=1000, blit=True)

References:

The implementation of this strategy is based on Houlsby et al.1 and Kirsch et al.2.

1

Neil Houlsby, Ferenc Huszár, Zoubin Ghahramani, and Máté Lengyel. Bayesian active learning for classification and preference learning. arXiv preprint arXiv:1112.5745, 2011.

2

Andreas Kirsch, Joost Van Amersfoort, and Yarin Gal. Batchbald: efficient and diverse batch acquisition for deep bayesian active learning. Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems, 2019.
